hopobject.body: A First Class stamp shine natural medicine reviews Chomsky was one of 25 Israeli girls on the way to Camp Simcha, a summer camp in Glen Spey, New York, for young people with cancer or other hematologic conditions. She was diagnosed with a life-threatening illness in May of 2012. Since then, the young girl has gone through rounds of radiation and chemotherapy, as well as surgery that has partially removed her tumor.
